The paper focuses on image retrieval using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and proposes a novel method for extracting discriminative representations containing regional information of small objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of trainable soft region proposals, indicating a possible connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a method that is free from bounding box annotations, which suggests a possible connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
